main event: An observer sighted a glowing object resembling a wide baseball bat 100 miles west of Milwaukee, Wisconsin, on January 27, 1968.
interesting points: The observed object was glowing white on the nose and blue white on the tail., The sighting lasted approximately 3-4 seconds., The object was seen to eject 10 glowing blue white balls on each side., There was a radar return from the object but no echoed response was observed., The object disappeared shortly after the balls were ejected.
sighted object: glowing object resembling a wide baseball bat
